</p>

<p corresp='TTP32804001P1' xml:id='OTP32804001P1'>[note] May 23, 1871 [/note]
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32804001P2' xml:id='OTP32804001P2'>State of Mississippi<lb/>
<rs ref='#S63223'>Carroll County</rs><lb/>
<hr/><lb/>
<rs ref='#S70054'>Circuit Court</rs>.<lb/>
Augt. Term 1870.
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32804001P3' xml:id='OTP32804001P3'>The <rs ref='#S63178'>Grand Jurors</rs> of the State of Mississippi, elected empannelled Sworn and Charged to enquire for the body of the County of Carroll Upon their Oaths present that <rs ref='#S32055042'>William Ringer</rs>, <rs ref='#S32055053'>Calhoun Applegate</rs>, &amp; <rs ref='#S32055043'>Henry Ringer</rs>, late of said County <rs ref='#S63442'>laborers</rs>, with force and arms in said County, on the 16th day of August 1870. Upon the body of <rs ref='#S32055041'>Arnold J Brantley</rs> in the peace of the said State there being—wilfully, feloniously, and of thier malice aforethought, did make an <rs ref='#S92354'>assault</rs>, and the said William Ringer Calhoun Applegate &amp; Henry Ringer him the said Arnold J Brantley, did then and there feloniously wilfully, &amp; of thier malice aforethought, <rs ref='#S63262'>Kill</rs> &amp; <rs ref='#S63926'>Murder</rs> Contrary to the Statute in such Case made &amp; provided, and against the peace &amp; dignity of the State of Mississippi
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32804001P4' xml:id='OTP32804001P4'><rs ref='#S32067557'>J C Stroup</rs><lb/>
<rs ref='#S94600'>District Attorney</rs>, 
</p>


        </div>
        <pb xml:id="F32804002" n="2" facs="https://cdm17313.contentdm.oclc.org/iiif/2/mdah:25506/full/full/0/default.jpg"/>
        <div xml:id="OTP32804002">
        <fw type="pageNum">Page 2</fw>
          <p corresp='TTP32804002P0' xml:id='OTP32804002P0'>Filed August 31<add place='above'>st</add> 1870<lb/>
<rs ref='#S32067558'>R C Hansbrough</rs> <rs ref='#S50807'>Clk</rs>
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32804002P1' xml:id='OTP32804002P1'>The State<lb/>
v <lb/>
<hr/><lb/>
Murder<lb/>
William Ringer<lb/>
Calhoun Applegate<lb/>
and<lb/>
Henry Ringer<lb/>
<hr/><lb/>
no <rs ref='#S25021515'>prosecutor</rs><lb/>
<hr/><lb/>
A True Bill<lb/>
<rs ref='#S25014416'>M M Liddell</rs><lb/>
Foreman of the Grand Jury.<lb/>
<hr/><lb/>
The State of Mississippi<lb/>
Carroll County
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32804002P2' xml:id='OTP32804002P2'>I R C Hansbrough Clerk of the Circuit Court in and for said County, do hereby Certify, that the within and foregoing is a true and Correct Copy of an <rs ref='#S95194'>Indictment</rs>, on file in my Office against. William Ringer, Calhoun Applegate, &amp; Henry Ringer, as the same remains on file in my Office,
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32804002P3' xml:id='OTP32804002P3'>Given under my hand &amp; seal of said Court this the 23<add place='above'>d</add> day of May AD 1871.
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32804002P4' xml:id='OTP32804002P4'>R C Hansbrough Clk
</p>


